Pre-heat your oven to 200 degrees. Peel and chop the @red onion{1} into 
bite-sized chunks. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and @yellow pepper{1} 
and chop into 3cm chunks. Chop the leafy green part and the base from the 
@leek{1}, then chop it widthways into 1cm thick discs. Chop the @cherry tomatoes{2} 
in half.

Toss your veggies in a splash of @olive oil{a splash} and a good pinch of 
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook them on a #baking tray{} in your oven for ~{20%minutes}.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{a splash} in a pan on medium heat and once hot add the
@chorizo{2}(diced). Cook for a few mins until ever so slightly crispy at the edges, 
then take the pan off the heat.

Dust your work surface with the @flour{2} (yep, we thought of everything!), roll 
the @Northern Dough Co. pizza dough{4} out into round pizza shapes, roughly 25cm 
across, and place on a lightly oiled baking tray.

> Tip: If you don't have a rolling pin you can always use a wine bottle wrapped 
> in clingfilm.

Spread the @tomato puree{3} thinly over each pizza base, leaving a border of 
around 2cm at the edge.

Once your veggies are soft, divide them between each pizza base (making sure you 
only cover one half of each base, so you can fold the other half over). Tear the 
@mozzarella{2} on top of your veggies and sprinkle over the @dried Italian herbs{2} 
and chorizo. Turn your oven to maximum temperature.

> Tip: To prevent the pizza base getting soggy, be careful not to add any excess 
> water from the vegetables.

To make your calzones, run a wet finger around the border of each pizza, then 
fold them over and press the edges down to seal. Cook on the top shelf of your 
oven for ~{8-10%minutes}. Job done!